BEEF ROULADE: The product must contain at least 50% cooked meat.
Usually a thin strip of flank meat wrapped around vegetables and cooked.
BEEF SLICES A-LA-PIZZAIOLA: The product must contain at least 50% cooked beef.
The label must show true product name, e.g., "Beef in Pizza Sauce."
BEEF STROGANOFF: A dish with a creamy sauce prepared with beef cut into narrow strips or cubes and sauteed.
Product labeled "Beef Stroganoff" should be prepared with a formula which includes at least 45% beef or 30% cooked beef.
