BONELESS BREAST TRIMMINGS: Boneless breast trimmings (turkey or chicken) are defined as trimmings that are removed from the breast portion only.
When a product is formulated with boneless breast trimmings, the amount of skin should be indicated in order to determine that the meat requirement is met for a standardized product and that the product is properly labeled.
Trimmings from the ribs may be identified as white turkey or white chicken trimmings, or white turkey or white chicken rib meat (excluding skin).
