HARDENED LARD: A fully hydrogenated flaked lard used for blending with other lard to raise smoke point and increase the stability and resistance to oxidation or development of rancidity.
HEAD MEAT: After removal of the cheeks, lips, snout, skin, and tongue from the head there remains small pockets and areas on the skull to which muscle tissue is attached.
This muscle may be removed and used in product and declared on labeling as beef or pork as the case may be.
However, there are a few standardized products in which the regulations limit theamount of this meat that may be used and require that it be specifically declared on the label (e.g., chili, chili with beans, and corned beef hash).
