FDA certified color additives require the listing of the common or usual names, e.g., FD
Color additives not subject to certification may be declared as "artificial color," "artificial color added," or "color added."
Alternatively, color additives not subject to certification may be declared as "colored with _______," or "________ color," with blank space filled in with the name of the color additive listed in 21 CFR 73, e.g., "colored with annatto" or "caramel color."
4.
Cured meat products used as ingredients, regardless of their level of use, require complete disclosure of all ingredients in the formulation of meat and poultry products.
