Mixtures of cereal, soy preparations and/or sodium caseinate with other substances are permitted to come into the plant for use in batter and gravy mixes, but they must be labeled to show their intended use, e.g., "Patty Mix" or "Gravy Mix."
The labels of the mixtures must show the ingredients in order of their predominance.
MOCK DRUMSTICKS: An imitation product; nonspecific.
MOCK TURTLE SOUP: Product must contain at least 10% beef and may be made with beef and beef byproducts.
